  <div class="calc-page__footer">
    <div class="calc-page__footer-title">Partnership K-1 Guidelines</div>
    <p>
      Schedule K-1 (Form 1065) reports each partner's share of partnership income, deductions,
      and credits. Qualifying income includes ordinary business income/loss (Line 1), net rental
      real estate income/loss (Lines 2/3), other net rental income/loss, and guaranteed payments
      to the partner (Line 4). Guaranteed payments are treated as stable income similar to a salary
      and are always added. If two years are provided and Year 1 exceeds Year 2, both years are
      averaged over 24 months; otherwise only the most recent year is used.
    </p>
